    def sinplot(n=10, flip=1):
    x = np.linspace(0, 14, 100)
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        plt.plot(x, np.sin(x + i * .5) * (n + 2 - i) * flip)
        # Chart Title
        plt.title('Sinewaves') 
        # Set Y Limits
        plt.ylim(ymin=-13,ymax=13)
        # Create Watermark
        plt.figtext(x=0.89, y=0.12, s="2023 Strictly Speaking", color='#757575', fontsize=13, 
        weight='ultralight', ha='right', va='bottom', transform=plt.gcf().transFigure) 

print(sinplot())
    def sinplot(n=10, flip=1): x = np.linspace(0, 14, 100) for i in range(1, n + 1): plt.plot(x, np.sin(x + i * .5) * (n + 2 - i) * flip) # Chart Title plt.title('Sinewaves') # Set Y Limits plt.ylim(ymin=-13,ymax=13) # Create Watermark plt.figtext(x=0.89, y=0.12, s="2023 Strictly Speaking", color='#757575', fontsize=13, weight='ultralight', ha='right', va='bottom', transform=plt.gcf().transFigure) print(sinplot())

    Clean Data¶

    The SP 500 Pricing data requires a few modifications.

    1) Remove the leading spaces within column names.

    2) Change the date column from object type data to datetime data.

    In [68]:
    Copied! 
    spx_data.rename(columns=lambda x: x.strip(), inplace=True)
print(spx_data.columns)
    spx_data.rename(columns=lambda x: x.strip(), inplace=True) print(spx_data.columns)
    Index(['Date', 'Open', 'High', 'Low', 'Close'], dtype='object')
    In [69]:
    Copied! 
    spx_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(spx_data['Date'])
print(f'The data type is: {spx_data["Date"].dtype}')
    spx_data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(spx_data['Date']) print(f'The data type is: {spx_data["Date"].dtype}')

    Object Oriented Charting¶

    More complex, but greater customization...

    In [73]:
    Copied! 
    with plt.style.context('default'):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,5))
    ax.plot(spx_data.Date,spx_data.Close)
    ax.set_title('Example Line Chart')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Level')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%m-%Y'))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.MonthLocator(interval=3))
    ax.spines['left'].set_visible(True)
    ax.spines['bottom'].set_visible(True)
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax.tick_params(bottom=True,left=True)
    ax.axhline(y=4400, c='grey',alpha=0.5)
plt.show()
    with plt.style.context('default'): fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,5)) ax.plot(spx_data.Date,spx_data.Close) ax.set_title('Example Line Chart') ax.set_xlabel('Date') ax.set_ylabel('Level') ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mdates.DateFormatter('%m-%Y')) ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(mdates.MonthLocator(interval=3)) ax.spines['left'].set_visible(True) ax.spines['bottom'].set_visible(True) ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False) ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False) ax.tick_params(bottom=True,left=True) ax.axhline(y=4400, c='grey',alpha=0.5) plt.show()
